1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:01,670
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,670 --> 00:00:03,380
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,380 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,650 --> 00:00:09,980
Father, I...

5
00:00:13,350 --> 00:00:14,490
I was wrong.

6
00:00:21,930 --> 00:00:22,990
You were wrong?

7
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:25,600
Yes.

8
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,770
To take over Temi Bio, I was told...

9
00:00:29,630 --> 00:00:31,270
that you killed CEO Baek Jun Gi...

10
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:34,310
and Jin Ju, the woman I loved,

11
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:38,440
and that it was the truth
behind the accident seven years ago.

12
00:00:50,590 --> 00:00:52,660
I lost my head
when Choi Yu Na told me that.

13
00:00:57,830 --> 00:00:58,900
But now,

14
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,730
you think differently?

15
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:06,040
Yes, I realized I was tricked.

16
00:01:07,810 --> 00:01:10,110
I've confirmed
that Choi Yu Na was drunk...

17
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:11,710
and that she lied to me.

18
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:14,380
Is that so?

19
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:17,020
Manager Kang!

20
00:01:21,390 --> 00:01:23,590
Get Choi Yu Na here right now.

21
00:01:24,460 --> 00:01:26,360
I need to confirm for myself...

22
00:01:27,190 --> 00:01:28,760
if she was really lying.

23
00:01:29,390 --> 00:01:30,400
Yes, sir.

24
00:01:43,810 --> 00:01:45,740
First, explain when, how,

25
00:01:47,010 --> 00:01:48,710
and why Choi Yu Na...

26
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:51,120
said those things.

27
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:54,950
While drinking alone
with Choi Yu Na,

28
00:01:55,150 --> 00:01:56,750
I told her I missed Jin Ju,

29
00:01:57,290 --> 00:01:59,220
and she lied, insisting
that I needed to forget her.

30
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:00,960
She probably thought...

31
00:02:01,530 --> 00:02:03,900
that if she said you'd killed
Baek Jun Gi and Jin Ju,

32
00:02:07,670 --> 00:02:10,270
I wouldn't even be able
to miss Jin Ju anymore.

33
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:15,410
Maybe she lied because she was drunk
or acting out of spite.

34
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:17,640
I see.

35
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:21,550
We'll see if Choi Yu Na's story...

36
00:02:22,380 --> 00:02:23,780
matches yours.

37
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:30,260
Ms. Choi is here.

38
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:42,030
Ms. Choi, you stood right here
and told me...

39
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:45,100
you hadn't said anything
inappropriate to my son...

40
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:47,070
and that you'd done nothing wrong.

41
00:02:47,910 --> 00:02:49,370
You made that very clear.

42
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,240
And yet,

43
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:56,710
he's telling me
he was fooled by your lies.

44
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:58,820
So explain yourself.

45
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,220
I lied?

46
00:03:12,230 --> 00:03:14,770
Tell me exactly what happened.

47
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,140
What Min Jun said...

48
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:23,270
is true.

49
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:31,620
What did you tell the chairman
before you left?

50
00:03:31,950 --> 00:03:34,350
Did you lie and say
I'm the one who told you everything?

51
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,520
Would that be lying?

52
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,820
Go tell the chairman...

53
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:41,830
that you found out yourself,
not through me.

54
00:03:41,860 --> 00:03:42,860
Someone did lie.

55
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:46,100
You were the one who lied to me,

56
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:49,500
and I was fooled by your lies
and misunderstood everything.

57
00:03:49,970 --> 00:03:52,270
I lied? You misunderstood me?

58
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:56,340
You'll say you knew nothing about
what happened seven years ago...

59
00:03:56,910 --> 00:03:58,780
and make me take all the blame?

60
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,010
Isn't that better for you too?

61
00:04:02,310 --> 00:04:05,950
If I say you told me everything
and that I won't forgive my father,

62
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:08,850
you'll have to deal
with the consequences...

63
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:10,520
if I stand against him.

64
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:11,520
So instead,

65
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:14,690
it'd be better for you if I said...

66
00:04:15,090 --> 00:04:16,390
I misunderstood your lies...

67
00:04:16,830 --> 00:04:18,400
and that nothing's changed.

68
00:04:21,530 --> 00:04:22,530
You may be forgiven...

69
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:25,170
for lying and making mistakes,

70
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:30,010
but never for telling the truth.

71
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:39,480
So go on and lie.
You're good at it, after all.

72
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:48,890
I'm sorry, sir.

73
00:04:49,530 --> 00:04:52,900
The truth is,
I was drunk and misspoke.

74
00:04:54,130 --> 00:04:57,370
Min Jun was drunk
and going on about Jin Ju,

75
00:04:57,940 --> 00:05:00,340
so I tried to tell him to move on
and forget her.

76
00:05:02,470 --> 00:05:04,110
Before I knew it, I was lying.

77
00:05:05,710 --> 00:05:08,680
And after all that,
you had the audacity to tell me...

78
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:10,420
you'd done nothing wrong?

79
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:13,580
I honestly didn't realize then
what I'd done.

80
00:05:16,220 --> 00:05:19,290
I was so drunk,
I didn't remember what I'd said.

81
00:05:19,890 --> 00:05:22,090
It wasn't until I met you
that it all came back to me.

82
00:05:22,460 --> 00:05:25,000
That's why I contacted Min Jun
to tell him the truth.

83
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:33,040
I was shaken by what Yu Na told me.

84
00:05:33,770 --> 00:05:36,940
But for you of all people...

85
00:05:38,010 --> 00:05:40,980
to hurt the woman
I loved like that...

86
00:05:44,650 --> 00:05:47,090
I realized it couldn't be true
and came to my senses.

87
00:05:48,490 --> 00:05:49,750
I was out of line.

88
00:05:50,590 --> 00:05:51,620
Please forgive me.

89
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,160
Sir,

90
00:05:55,690 --> 00:05:58,760
Ms. Choi spoke carelessly,
and Min Jun misunderstood.

91
00:05:59,930 --> 00:06:01,400
Please forgive him.

92
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:04,700
No.

93
00:06:06,540 --> 00:06:07,940
Forgive him? Don't be ridiculous.

94
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:11,410
Honey, they're all trying
to fool you.

95
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:12,940
I see...

96
00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:16,080
right through the shameless act
the three of you cooked up.

97
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,780
What charade are you talking about?

98
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:22,820
You all know what's going on.
You're just playing dumb.

99
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:25,960
We all knew?
That's a strange thing to say.

100
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:30,290
What's there to know about something
the chairman didn't even do?

101
00:06:30,930 --> 00:06:31,930
Hold on.

102
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:36,800
Are you suggesting the chairman
actually committed murder?

103
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,600
What?

104
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:43,670
No, that's not what I meant.

105
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:44,680
Enough!

106
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:47,380
We're settling this matter
here and now.

107
00:06:48,350 --> 00:06:50,720
Everyone but Park Min Jun, get out.

108
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:11,140
You two-faced liars.

109
00:07:14,410 --> 00:07:16,840
You. Tell me the truth.

110
00:07:17,310 --> 00:07:19,710
I bet you and Min Jun are trying
to fool the chairman.

111
00:07:20,380 --> 00:07:22,150
What do you mean
we're deceiving him?

112
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:23,510
She's right.

113
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,120
If what Ms. Choi said was true,

114
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:28,150
then that's what really happened
seven years ago.

115
00:07:28,150 --> 00:07:29,750
Why are you insisting that it was?

116
00:07:30,620 --> 00:07:32,990
You're going to give everyone
the wrong idea.

117
00:07:37,930 --> 00:07:39,260
So let me get this straight.

118
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:42,470
Choi Yu Na, are you saying
you got drunk and lied?

119
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,540
That the CEO Baek of Temi Bio...

120
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:48,710
Park Hyun Jun.
Why do you keep saying that name?

121
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,680
What if your father hears you?

122
00:07:51,210 --> 00:07:53,640
Go upstairs. Go on, now.

123
00:07:53,810 --> 00:07:55,210
Get upstairs already.

124
00:08:00,550 --> 00:08:03,150
Are you still upset with me?

125
00:08:12,830 --> 00:08:14,930
Listen. I need to confirm something.

126
00:08:16,470 --> 00:08:17,870
In your office,

127
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:20,570
I came across some files
on Temi Bio.

128
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:23,910
Oh, that.

129
00:08:25,010 --> 00:08:26,780
I was reviewing the records...

130
00:08:27,610 --> 00:08:28,610
the company still had.

131
00:08:29,410 --> 00:08:30,410
Why?

132
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:35,750
I wanted to help my mom when she was
named president of the bio division.

133
00:08:36,420 --> 00:08:38,420
I wasn't familiar
with the Temi Bio merger,

134
00:08:38,420 --> 00:08:40,420
so I decided to look into it.

135
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:45,930
I'll make sure
there's nothing for you...

136
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:48,370
to worry about, sir.

137
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:54,370
I'm not your chairman.
I'm your father.

138
00:08:55,770 --> 00:08:58,240
What you did wasn't
against the chairman.

139
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,480
It was against me, your father.

140
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:04,850
Make no mistake, you are my son,

141
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,120
and I won't tolerate any talk...

142
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:10,450
of severing ties with me.

143
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:15,130
I'm your son, through and through?

144
00:09:16,530 --> 00:09:18,160
The son of a murderer.

145
00:09:20,770 --> 00:09:24,000
Whether you see me as your father...

146
00:09:24,740 --> 00:09:26,600
or as something else...

147
00:09:27,510 --> 00:09:28,970
I suppose time will tell.

148
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,100
What is it?

149
00:09:55,370 --> 00:09:56,700
Is there something else
you have to say?

150
00:09:58,470 --> 00:10:01,270
Don't forget
what I did for you this time.

151
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:04,310
And make sure
he never finds out you know.

152
00:10:05,010 --> 00:10:06,510
It'll put me in danger too.

153
00:10:06,610 --> 00:10:08,050
Don't kid yourself.

154
00:10:09,050 --> 00:10:12,720
You didn't help me. I used you.

155
00:10:14,420 --> 00:10:15,420
What?

156
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:18,020
And you'd better not forget either.

157
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:22,190
When I said
I'd get revenge for Jin Ju,

158
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:24,460
I meant every word.

159
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:25,760
Revenge?

160
00:10:28,370 --> 00:10:30,370
If you come after me
because of Jin Ju,

161
00:10:30,470 --> 00:10:32,400
you're coming
after the chairman too.

162
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:36,240
You really think
you can take him on?

163
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:39,740
I'd worry more about yourself.

164
00:10:56,260 --> 00:10:57,260
Mother.

165
00:11:06,370 --> 00:11:07,740
You've been through so much.

166
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:12,680
I know what it took for you
to come back...

167
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:17,580
and the painful choice
you had to make.

168
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:21,690
I know that better than anyone.

169
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:25,760
Because I once made
that same choice,

170
00:11:26,390 --> 00:11:28,630
feeling the way you do now.

171
00:11:34,570 --> 00:11:36,730
I think I understand
how you feel now.

172
00:11:46,180 --> 00:11:48,280
You said you wanted the power
that Adele can give you.

173
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:52,920
You need power to find the truth
and do what's right.

174
00:11:54,850 --> 00:11:57,860
I also need the power...

175
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:00,190
of Adele.

176
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:02,430
That's why I came back.

177
00:12:03,030 --> 00:12:04,330
You mean...

178
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:07,130
you'll go against your own father?

179
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:11,570
I have to right my father's wrongs.

180
00:12:16,870 --> 00:12:17,880
I...

181
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,550
want to take over Adele.

182
00:12:37,290 --> 00:12:38,360
Park Hyun Jun.

183
00:12:38,730 --> 00:12:40,900
Why are you saying
such reckless things?

184
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:44,170
It's reckless to talk
about Temi Bio?

185
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:50,910
I'm asking you one last time,
so tell me what you know.

186
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:53,680
Did Father hurt
Temi Bio's CEO, Baek Jun Gi...

187
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:54,680
Stop.

188
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:57,250
Why do you keep going on
about Temi Bio?

189
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:59,420
You're just like
that punk Min Jun...

190
00:13:01,590 --> 00:13:02,590
Wait a minute.

191
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:05,090
You've been acting strange
ever since you came down.

192
00:13:06,260 --> 00:13:10,430
What did you hear that made you
challenge your father like that?

193
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:15,130
I saw Park Min Jun's Temi Bio file.
There was a memo inside.

194
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:20,070
It wasn't just a car accident,
but an explosion Father ordered.

195
00:13:20,370 --> 00:13:21,740
A file on Temi Bio?

196
00:13:22,710 --> 00:13:24,340
How did you get your hands on that?

197
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:29,580
President Kim asked me to put them
in Min Jun's room for her.

198
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:30,850
What?

199
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:33,580
Are you saying
she put those files...

200
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:35,450
directly in your hands?

201
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:38,220
That's not
what's important right now.

202
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:41,290
Weren't you listening earlier?

203
00:13:41,860 --> 00:13:43,960
Even that jerk Park Min Jun
admitted he was duped.

204
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:48,100
So just drop it.
Don't give it another thought.

205
00:13:48,230 --> 00:13:51,670
Don't say a single word
that will set your father off.

206
00:13:51,940 --> 00:13:52,940
Got it?

207
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:07,590
Choi Yu Na.

208
00:14:10,190 --> 00:14:11,520
She was lying, wasn't she?

209
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:16,260
This is important to me too!

210
00:14:16,260 --> 00:14:18,260
Then you should've looked
into it sooner.

211
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:21,700
What's this?

212
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:23,930
The way you're acting,

213
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:27,200
it sounds like the Temi Bio incident
from seven years ago was real.

214
00:14:32,410 --> 00:14:35,680
If I told you Choi Yu Na was lying,
would you just let it go?

215
00:14:35,780 --> 00:14:37,150
Do you really have no intention...

216
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,020
of finding out
what happened seven years ago?

217
00:14:43,050 --> 00:14:45,560
I tried to find out
what happened, okay?

218
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:50,090
I even asked our father to his face
if he'd killed someone.

219
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:53,660
But after listening to you,

220
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:56,600
I'm starting to think...

221
00:14:57,530 --> 00:14:58,970
the truth doesn't even matter
anymore.

222
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,410
What?

223
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:02,770
Whatever the truth is,

224
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:06,040
I don't think
I'll change my mind either way.

225
00:15:06,510 --> 00:15:07,880
No matter the reason,

226
00:15:09,650 --> 00:15:11,450
I won't let go of the woman I love.

227
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:17,250
So even at the very end,

228
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:19,390
you'll still only think
about yourself?

229
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:22,190
Fine.

230
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:24,600
If that's your choice,
do what you will.

231
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:25,630
But...

232
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,700
if that choice of yours...

233
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,770
ends up hurting Jin Ju,

234
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:36,240
there will be a price to pay.

235
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:48,950
You'll make me pay?

236
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:51,260
Fine.

237
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:53,360
Bring it on.

238
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:58,200
I won't lose to you...

239
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,300
or to the truth.

240
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:09,470
Stop that and have a seat.

241
00:16:09,810 --> 00:16:11,980
In any case,
we really dodged a bullet.

242
00:16:13,010 --> 00:16:14,010
We dodged a bullet?

243
00:16:14,610 --> 00:16:17,250
Thanks to Park Min Jun stepping in
and saying he was tricked,

244
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:20,650
Hyun Jun gets to move on
without knowing a thing.

245
00:16:21,590 --> 00:16:25,160
As long as our Hyun Jun
wasn't shocked or hurt,

246
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:27,160
that's all that matters.

247
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:30,490
As if.

248
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:34,300
Kim Myung Hui and Park Min Jun know
what happened seven years ago.

249
00:16:34,370 --> 00:16:38,500
But you're the one
who told President Kim about it.

250
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:43,410
Fine. I shot myself in the foot.
Happy now?

251
00:16:44,380 --> 00:16:46,640
I'm just telling you not to worry.

252
00:16:48,310 --> 00:16:50,880
It's not like anything will change
just because they know.

253
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:52,780
Always so clueless.

254
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:56,820
Kim Myung Hui and Park Min Jun
won't just let this go.

255
00:16:57,650 --> 00:16:59,020
On top of that, Kim Myung Hui...

256
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:03,260
dragged Hyun Jun into this
by bringing up Munhwadang and Temi Bio.

257
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:06,360
We can't just let them
get away with this.

258
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:09,970
If you stay out of it,
they won't bother Hyun Jun either.

259
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,540
You should just...

260
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:16,740
lie low, okay? Just let it be.

261
00:17:17,110 --> 00:17:20,640
Even if something does happen,
Chairman Park will take care of it.

262
00:17:21,850 --> 00:17:25,050
You know him.
He's probably already planning...

263
00:17:25,120 --> 00:17:26,920
how to handle this.

264
00:17:26,950 --> 00:17:29,250
Park Tae Ho will do his thing,
and I'll do mine.

265
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:32,260
If they mess with Hyun Jun again,

266
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:35,190
I swear I'll take this
all the way to the end.

267
00:17:38,460 --> 00:17:39,460
Right.

268
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:43,900
Have someone follow Min Jun.

269
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,170
And as for Choi Yu Na...

270
00:17:50,540 --> 00:17:52,510
It's time I silenced her.

271
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:01,190
Is it that bad?

272
00:18:01,620 --> 00:18:06,220
How could he be okay?
The scare with Clyde was bad enough,

273
00:18:06,290 --> 00:18:08,230
but Park Tae Ho made it worse.

274
00:18:08,660 --> 00:18:09,760
Unbelievable.

275
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:12,360
All this and that.

276
00:18:12,430 --> 00:18:14,600
I should send that jerk the bill
for everything.

277
00:18:14,830 --> 00:18:19,540
Stop it. If you do that,
who knows what he'll do to us?

278
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:23,370
Yu Na,
has it all been taken care of?

279
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,580
That's what I said.

280
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:27,340
I cleared it up
as a misunderstanding yesterday.

281
00:18:27,410 --> 00:18:28,850
Misunderstanding or not,

282
00:18:29,450 --> 00:18:31,880
him and his goons stormed
into our house,

283
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:34,990
trashed the place,
and wrecked everything.

284
00:18:35,420 --> 00:18:38,490
If I could act on my anger,

285
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:40,590
I'd go over there
and wreck their whole house...

286
00:18:40,590 --> 00:18:44,730
Mom, just stop.
Don't make things more complicated.

287
00:18:45,030 --> 00:18:48,430
You darn brat.
Why are you taking it out on me?

288
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,870
Don't be so hard on her.
Let's go to the doctor for now.

289
00:18:54,770 --> 00:18:57,470
If anything happens,
call me right away,

290
00:18:58,140 --> 00:18:59,940
and make sure you lock up.

291
00:19:00,510 --> 00:19:01,780
For crying out loud.

292
00:19:03,850 --> 00:19:05,250
Make sure you lock up.

293
00:19:07,580 --> 00:19:09,990
I've handled things
with Park Min Jun for now,

294
00:19:10,950 --> 00:19:13,020
but I'm out of moves.

295
00:19:15,060 --> 00:19:16,530
How do I get back in the game?

296
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,960
How am I supposed to get
what I want now?

297
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:27,910
What is it this time?

298
00:19:29,070 --> 00:19:32,040
I figured you'd have that look
on your face.

299
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:33,710
What?

300
00:19:33,710 --> 00:19:37,610
I heard Park Min Jun left home
over what happened seven years ago.

301
00:19:37,780 --> 00:19:41,920
You slipped up, and he heard us
talking on the phone.

302
00:19:42,750 --> 00:19:46,360
I stopped by the chairman's office,
and it seems he knows too.

303
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:51,430
Did your attempt to blackmail
the chairman backfire on you?

304
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:56,170
I see you only know half the story.

305
00:19:56,670 --> 00:19:59,740
Park Min Jun came home last night.

306
00:20:00,770 --> 00:20:01,770
He did?

307
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:06,510
I told the chairman I misspoke,
and I was forgiven.

308
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:09,050
Forgiven?

309
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:12,480
Because of you, I played hardball
and almost ended up...

310
00:20:12,550 --> 00:20:13,820
in deep trouble.

311
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:17,920
I'm relieved you were forgiven,

312
00:20:18,260 --> 00:20:22,090
but what about your plan
to use Park Min Jun as leverage?

313
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:27,060
That's useless now, isn't it?

314
00:20:27,860 --> 00:20:30,700
And you're happy
just because he forgave you,

315
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:33,470
even though you have no way back
into the company...

316
00:20:33,470 --> 00:20:35,770
and no leverage over Chairman Park?

317
00:20:42,450 --> 00:20:44,580
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

318
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:48,920
Yes, Chairman Park.

319
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:54,160
Yes, I understand.
I'll be there on time.

320
00:20:56,890 --> 00:20:58,260
What did Chairman Park say?

321
00:20:58,330 --> 00:20:59,900
He wants to see me privately.

322
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,400
Why?

323
00:21:02,930 --> 00:21:06,000
He's probably just double-checking
what happened yesterday.

324
00:21:09,040 --> 00:21:11,410
That's between him and me,
so you don't need to know.

325
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,440
Just you watch.

326
00:21:13,610 --> 00:21:16,610
I'll find another way
or another angle if I must.

327
00:21:17,750 --> 00:21:18,950
When I meet with the chairman,

328
00:21:18,950 --> 00:21:20,480
I'll use my father's shares
if I have to,

329
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:22,250
to get my job back at the company.

330
00:21:23,450 --> 00:21:28,030
If you think I've lost my leverage,
that you won't get the bio division,

331
00:21:28,090 --> 00:21:29,590
and that this is a bad deal for you,

332
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,430
then break off our deal
and get lost.

333
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:36,170
Fine. Then I guess
I should back out.

334
00:21:40,940 --> 00:21:43,070
Here's a piece of advice...

335
00:21:43,070 --> 00:21:45,440
from someone
who was briefly your partner.

336
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:49,410
Don't trust Chairman Park Tae Ho
too much.

337
00:21:50,650 --> 00:21:54,150
From what I've seen,
he's not the forgiving type.

338
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:02,830
As if I don't already know that.

339
00:22:04,130 --> 00:22:05,830
It's not that he's forgiven me.

340
00:22:06,260 --> 00:22:09,030
He's calling me
because I'm still useful to him.

341
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:13,670
I have to do whatever it takes,
somehow create an opportunity,

342
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:15,840
and get my job back.

343
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:40,030
I told you to lay low
and pretend you knew nothing.

344
00:22:40,630 --> 00:22:42,300
How could you fight
with Chairman Park...

345
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:43,570
and then storm out of the house?

346
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:46,970
Were you worried about me?

347
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:53,980
I wasn't worried about you.
I was worried about myself.

348
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:56,450
I was worried you'd interfere
with my plans.

349
00:22:58,950 --> 00:23:00,780
Chairman Park is going
to be suspicious now.

350
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:03,750
That won't happen.

351
00:23:04,420 --> 00:23:06,460
I said Choi Yu Na lied
while drunk...

352
00:23:06,460 --> 00:23:08,090
and that it was
all a misunderstanding.

353
00:23:09,760 --> 00:23:11,290
I even took Choi Yu Na
to him myself,

354
00:23:11,860 --> 00:23:13,430
and sold him our story.

355
00:23:13,530 --> 00:23:15,230
And Chairman Park bought that?

356
00:23:15,330 --> 00:23:16,730
He'll still be suspicious,

357
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:21,910
but it's my job to work around that,
so don't worry.

358
00:23:22,540 --> 00:23:23,540
You're making a move?

359
00:23:23,670 --> 00:23:25,710
Let's just say I have a new goal.

360
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:29,980
I wouldn't dare say I love you
or that I want you back,

361
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:34,350
but I'm not the same man
I was seven years ago.

362
00:23:35,750 --> 00:23:37,820
Everything I do from now on...

363
00:23:38,220 --> 00:23:41,120
is because I want to be a better man
than I was back then.

364
00:23:41,530 --> 00:23:43,960
It's for my sake, not yours.

365
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,960
So don't worry
or give it a second thought.

366
00:23:53,170 --> 00:23:54,370
I should get going.

367
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:02,210
You're lying.

368
00:24:04,310 --> 00:24:06,520
Even your lies...

369
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:09,350
are all for my sake.

370
00:24:24,070 --> 00:24:28,510
Choi Yu Na lied,
and Chairman Park just forgave her?

371
00:24:30,140 --> 00:24:31,140
It's me.

372
00:24:31,710 --> 00:24:34,240
I've got something we can use
to pressure Chairman Park.

373
00:24:34,850 --> 00:24:36,910
A secret that Park Min Jun
must never find out.

374
00:24:39,950 --> 00:24:40,950
All right.

375
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:45,360
I'll take it from here.

376
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:50,630
Chairman Park isn't
the forgiving type.

377
00:24:51,130 --> 00:24:52,130
Not at all.

378
00:24:57,370 --> 00:24:58,640
How's Min Jun?

379
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:01,740
He dove right into work
as soon as he got in.

380
00:25:02,070 --> 00:25:05,080
He's targeting high-profile projects
with clear results.

381
00:25:05,580 --> 00:25:08,450
I think he's trying to win over
the board and the shareholders.

382
00:25:09,610 --> 00:25:12,550
We should help him.
What's your first move?

383
00:25:12,620 --> 00:25:14,850
He can handle the business side
on his own.

384
00:25:15,750 --> 00:25:18,560
My job is to stand in the way
of Chairman Park and Oh Jung Ran.

385
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:21,590
Chairman Park
will keep suspecting Min Jun,

386
00:25:21,590 --> 00:25:25,360
and Oh Jung Ran will keep trying
to drive a wedge between them.

387
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:28,530
Then let's neutralize Oh Jung Ran,

388
00:25:28,930 --> 00:25:32,870
and prove Min Jun is
the only qualified successor.

389
00:25:33,940 --> 00:25:35,240
Oh Jung Ran's secret.

390
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:37,870
You're suggesting we use
the Munhwadang incident against her.

391
00:25:41,410 --> 00:25:43,180
Jung Ran!

392
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:45,450
It's bad!

393
00:25:46,780 --> 00:25:48,080
Quiet down.

394
00:25:48,620 --> 00:25:50,220
Why are you yelling like that?

395
00:25:50,550 --> 00:25:52,360
Because it's bad!

396
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:54,660
The Munhwadang incident.

397
00:25:55,490 --> 00:25:58,730
Everyone knows what you did now!

398
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:00,160
What?

399
00:26:00,230 --> 00:26:03,770
Someone shared it
in the Adele investors' group,

400
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:08,240
and now everyone's up in arms
saying they won't let it slide.

401
00:26:23,020 --> 00:26:24,020
Unbelievable, right?

402
00:26:26,890 --> 00:26:29,330
(Adele, Brightening Your Tomorrow)

403
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:37,970
What the heck?

404
00:26:41,570 --> 00:26:43,270
(Investors' Forum:
Is Adele's Oh Jung Ran a murderer?)

405
00:26:48,210 --> 00:26:50,950
Don't just stand here.
Go home or go back to your office.

406
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:53,920
Hey, that's Oh Jung Ran's son
over there.

407
00:26:54,180 --> 00:26:56,650
- You're right. Look who it is.
- There he is.

408
00:26:57,750 --> 00:27:00,120
Did your mother really kill someone?

409
00:27:01,090 --> 00:27:02,560
You must know something, right?

410
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:03,830
Never mind that.

411
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:07,700
The stock price tanked.
How will you pay for my losses?

412
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:09,470
Everybody, that's enough.

413
00:27:10,470 --> 00:27:11,970
Get out of here. Hurry.

414
00:27:13,370 --> 00:27:16,010
Where do you think
you're going? Hey!

415
00:27:16,070 --> 00:27:19,610
Move! Enough!

416
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:22,780
How dare you lay a hand on him?

417
00:27:23,110 --> 00:27:25,420
- Hyun Jun, are you okay?
- Hey!

418
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:26,950
You're Oh Jung Ran, right?

419
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:29,220
That's right. So what?

420
00:27:29,950 --> 00:27:32,890
I heard you used to be
the lady of Munhwadang's maid.

421
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:35,390
Did you really kill
the woman you worked for?

422
00:27:36,660 --> 00:27:38,700
Who said that?
Do you have any proof?

423
00:27:39,260 --> 00:27:42,570
Keep spreading baseless accusations,
and I'll sue you for defamation!

424
00:27:42,630 --> 00:27:43,630
Whatever.

425
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:47,600
Do you have any idea how much money
I lost on my stocks because of you?

426
00:27:47,970 --> 00:27:52,240
How is that my fault?
I'm the victim of all your rumors.

427
00:27:52,340 --> 00:27:54,680
- A victim?
- Give me back my money.

428
00:27:54,740 --> 00:27:57,680
- What about our money?
- My money!

429
00:27:57,680 --> 00:27:58,950
- You!
- Give us our money.

430
00:27:59,020 --> 00:28:00,580
- You tramp!
- Hyun Jun!

431
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:01,850
- Give us our money!
- What will you do about this?

432
00:28:01,850 --> 00:28:03,750
- You're done for.
- My money!

433
00:28:04,190 --> 00:28:07,560
- Hey, what are you going to do?
- What about our money?

434
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:08,830
What will you do about this?

435
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:15,200
Seriously, what are you going to do?

436
00:28:16,430 --> 00:28:18,230
That Kim Myung Hui, I swear...

437
00:28:18,670 --> 00:28:20,800
I can't believe
she could just kill someone.

438
00:28:21,670 --> 00:28:23,310
I can't believe this.

439
00:28:27,540 --> 00:28:29,850
Someone should do something.

440
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:41,360
Hyun Jun.

441
00:28:42,130 --> 00:28:43,130
Hyun Jun.

442
00:28:43,430 --> 00:28:46,330
Hyun Jun, honey. Let me explain.

443
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:48,970
What...

444
00:28:51,270 --> 00:28:53,700
What kind of people are you and Dad?

445
00:28:55,270 --> 00:28:58,140
What secrets from the past
are you hiding?

446
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:02,380
- Hyun Jun, please.
- This is why...

447
00:29:02,810 --> 00:29:05,620
I have no choice
but to be a selfish brat.

448
00:29:06,850 --> 00:29:08,450
I have to pretend
none of it matters,

449
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:11,720
even whether my parents
killed someone.

450
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:17,760
Because I can't bear looking guilty
in front of the person I love most.

451
00:29:20,460 --> 00:29:23,000
Because I refuse to live
as a murderer's son!

452
00:29:23,870 --> 00:29:24,870
What?

453
00:29:26,070 --> 00:29:28,740
A murderer's son?

454
00:29:29,810 --> 00:29:30,870
Hyun Jun.

455
00:29:31,140 --> 00:29:32,140
Mom...

456
00:29:32,980 --> 00:29:35,410
I expected this from Dad,
but not from you.

457
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:39,180
If you're like him too, then I...

458
00:29:40,950 --> 00:29:42,320
Then I can't take it.

459
00:29:46,220 --> 00:29:48,390
No, that's not who I am.

460
00:29:51,830 --> 00:29:53,130
Whatever you did, Mom,

461
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:55,730
I don't care what the truth is.

462
00:29:58,130 --> 00:30:00,840
Just don't let this turn me
into a murderer's son.

463
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:03,510
In front of everyone... No.

464
00:30:04,340 --> 00:30:06,210
Especially not in front of
that jerk Park Min Jun,

465
00:30:08,680 --> 00:30:10,410
I won't bow my head.

466
00:30:21,260 --> 00:30:22,590
Jung Ran, are you okay?

467
00:30:23,330 --> 00:30:24,930
Poor Hyun Jun.

468
00:30:25,760 --> 00:30:29,330
He must be taking this really hard.
What are we going to do?

469
00:30:31,170 --> 00:30:32,940
This is all Kim Myung Hui's fault.

470
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:35,770
Kim Myung Hui.

471
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:07,600
What's going on?

472
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:11,210
Why isn't there anyone
at the warehouse?

473
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:13,610
Why would the chairman...

474
00:31:18,080 --> 00:31:19,080
Wait.

475
00:31:20,350 --> 00:31:21,420
Something's not right.

476
00:31:47,340 --> 00:31:48,880
(Incoming Call)

477
00:31:51,980 --> 00:31:55,250
(Incoming Call)

478
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:42,630
(Pearl in Red)

479
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:46,140
What is this?
Some kind of sick joke?

480
00:32:46,270 --> 00:32:48,340
Jin Ju was in an accident.
She's in the hospital.

481
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:49,470
It should end here.

482
00:32:49,470 --> 00:32:52,180
If you want revenge,
find another way.

483
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:55,750
Did you really kill
the woman you served?

484
00:32:55,750 --> 00:32:59,350
Did you drug the lady of Munhwadang
and kill her?

485
00:32:59,350 --> 00:33:02,650
Honey, I can still be useful.
I'll do anything.

486
00:33:02,650 --> 00:33:05,860
You'll do anything I tell you to do?

487
00:33:06,260 --> 00:33:08,260
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
